            <fr:title text="Forester 2.3">Forester 2.3</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Release</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p><fr:link href="foreign-forester-arma%C3%ABlgu%C3%A9neau.xml" title="Armaël Guéneau" addr="forest://forester/arma%C3%ABlgu%C3%A9neau" type="local">Armaël Guéneau</fr:link>, <fr:link href="foreign-forester-rileyshahar.xml" title="Riley Shahar" addr="forest://forester/rileyshahar" type="local">Riley Shahar</fr:link>, and <fr:link href="foreign-forester-jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="forest://forester/jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link> contributed code to this major release. Thanks also to <fr:link href="foreign-forester-masanoriogino.xml" title="Masanori Ogino" addr="forest://forester/masanoriogino" type="local">Masanori Ogino</fr:link> for <fr:link href="foreign-forester-jms-0072.xml" title="Rudimentary support for XML attributes" addr="forest://forester/jms-0072" type="local">feature requests</fr:link> that made it into this release.</fr:p>
            <fr:p>This release adds some new features to the command line interface. The original behavior of the <fr:code>forester</fr:code> command is now obtained by calling <fr:code>forester build</fr:code>. Please browse <fr:code>forester --help</fr:code> for more information.</fr:p>
            <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
              <fr:frontmatter>
                <fr:authors>
                  <fr:author>
                    <fr:link href="foreign-forester-jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="forest://forester/jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
                  </fr:author>
                </fr:authors>
                <fr:date>
                  <fr:year>2023</fr:year>
                  <fr:month>8</fr:month>
                  <fr:day>14</fr:day>
                </fr:date>
                <fr:addr>forest://forester/jms-0070</fr:addr>
                <fr:route>foreign-forester-jms-0070.xml</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="Create new trees from the command line">Create new trees from the command line</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Feature</fr:taxon>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <fr:p>A new command has been added in <fr:link href="foreign-forester-jms-006Z.xml" title="Forester 2.3" addr="forest://forester/jms-006Z" type="local">Forester 2.3</fr:link> to simplify the creation of new trees with the correct base-36 identifier. If your personal namespace prefix is <fr:code>xxx</fr:code>, you may run the following command to create a new tree in the <fr:code>trees</fr:code> directory:</fr:p>
                <fr:pre><![CDATA[forester new --dir=trees --prefix=xxx]]></fr:pre>
                <fr:p>If the last tree in this directory was <fr:code>xxx-0039</fr:code>, a new tree will be generated at <fr:code>xxx-003A</fr:code>. The new tree will be populated with a correct <fr:code><![CDATA[\date]]></fr:code> declaration.</fr:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
            <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
              <fr:frontmatter>
