                  </fr:author>
                </fr:authors>
                <fr:date>
                  <fr:year>2023</fr:year>
                  <fr:month>8</fr:month>
                  <fr:day>14</fr:day>
                </fr:date>
                <fr:addr>forest://forester/jms-0071</fr:addr>
                <fr:route>foreign-forester-jms-0071.xml</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="Tree title completion for tool support">Tree title completion for tool support</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Feature</fr:taxon>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <fr:p>A new <fr:code>forester complete</fr:code> command has been added to search for trees by their title; the purpose of this command is to facilitate external tool support, such as this <fr:link href="https://github.com/rileyshahar/cmp-Forester" type="external">proof-of-concept completion engine for neovim</fr:link>. Please browse <fr:code>forester complete --help</fr:code> for more information about this command.</fr:p>
                <fr:p>Current limitations: the command is currently case sensitive and only searches prefixes; in the future, it would be desirable to support more flexible <fr:link href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Approximate_string_matching" type="external">fuzzy-search</fr:link>.</fr:p>
                <fr:p>Thanks to <fr:link href="foreign-forester-rileyshahar.xml" title="Riley Shahar" addr="forest://forester/rileyshahar" type="local">Riley Shahar</fr:link> for implementing this feature.</fr:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
            <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
              <fr:frontmatter>
                <fr:authors>
                  <fr:author>
                    <fr:link href="foreign-forester-jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="forest://forester/jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
                  </fr:author>
                </fr:authors>
                <fr:date>
                  <fr:year>2023</fr:year>
                  <fr:month>8</fr:month>
                  <fr:day>14</fr:day>
                </fr:date>
                <fr:addr>forest://forester/jms-0072</fr:addr>
                <fr:route>foreign-forester-jms-0072.xml</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="Rudimentary support for XML attributes">Rudimentary support for XML attributes</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Feature</fr:taxon>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <fr:p>When Forester encounters an undefined function, it automatically passes through to the XML output. For instance, if the function <fr:code><![CDATA[\myfun]]></fr:code> is not defined, then the Forester code <fr:code><![CDATA[\myfun{hello}]]></fr:code> will render to the XML code <fr:code><![CDATA[<myfun>hello</myfun>]]></fr:code>. <fr:strong>The <fr:link href="foreign-forester-jms-006Z.xml" title="Forester 2.3" addr="forest://forester/jms-006Z" type="local">Forester 2.3</fr:link> extends this fall-through behavior to support XML attributes.</fr:strong></fr:p>
                <fr:p>In particular, if you write <fr:code><![CDATA[\myfun{key1}{value1}{key2}{value2}{hello}]]></fr:code>, Forester will render the following XML code:</fr:p>
                <fr:pre><![CDATA[<myfun key1="value1" key2="value2">
  hello
</myfun>]]></fr:pre>
                <fr:p>Thanks to <fr:link href="foreign-forester-masanoriogino.xml" title="Masanori Ogino" addr="forest://forester/masanoriogino" type="local">Masanori Ogino</fr:link> for suggesting this feature, and welcome to the <fr:link href="https://lists.sr.ht/~jonsterling/forester-discuss" type="external">Forester community</fr:link>!.</fr:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
            <fr:p>In addition to the major changes above, the following minor changes are included in this release:</fr:p>
            <fr:ol><fr:li>A <fr:code>title</fr:code> attribute attribute has been added to the XML output of internal links, in order to facilitate tooltips and other affordances in rendered forests. Thanks to <fr:link href="foreign-forester-arma%C3%ABlgu%C3%A9neau.xml" title="Armaël Guéneau" addr="forest://forester/arma%C3%ABlgu%C3%A9neau" type="local">Armaël Guéneau</fr:link> for implementing this feature.</fr:li>
  <fr:li>Subdirectories of input directories will now be traversed automatically; note that the tree address model remains flat, and subdirectories are present only for convenience.</fr:li>
  <fr:li>Added a nicer command line interface with <fr:code>--help</fr:code> documentation.</fr:li>
  <fr:li>I have migrated much of the system code to use the experimental <fr:link href="https://github.com/ocaml-multicore/eio" type="external">Eio library</fr:link> for improved portability.</fr:li>
  <fr:li>The example forest has been removed from the main repository, and moved into a separate <fr:link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/forest-template" type="external">template repository</fr:link>.</fr:li></fr:ol>
          </fr:mainmatter>
